{"id": "EUVD-2020-0270", "enisaUuid": "a7984ff6-b898-3829-a301-ed2cdfb1f331", "description": "Opencast before 7.6 and 8.1 enables a remember-me cookie based on a hash created from the username, password, and an additional system key. This means that an attacker getting access to a remember-me token for one server can get access to all servers which allow log-in using the same credentials without ever needing the credentials. This problem is fixed in Opencast 7.6 and Opencast 8.1", "datePublished": "2020-01-30T20:50:13", "dateUpdated": "2024-08-04T08:22:08", "baseScore": 6.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:N/AC:L/PR:L/UI:R/S:C/C:H/I:N/A:N", "references": ["https://github.com/opencast/opencast/security/advisories/GHSA-mh8g-hprg-8363", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2020-5222", "https://github.com/opencast/opencast/commit/1a7172c95af8d542a77ae5b153e4c834dd4788a6"], "aliases": ["CVE-2020-5222", "GHSA-mh8g-hprg-8363"], "assigner": "GitHub_M", "epss": 0.26, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "aff0e900-975b-3fea-ae2c-20639555bc6b", "product": {"name": "opencast"}, "product_version": "8.0, < 8.1"}, {"id": "b42bbc21-cebc-3bec-aa95-d6613a273c61", "product": {"name": "opencast"}, "product_version": "< 7.6"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "7aba6ec0-6b9f-34ec-9326-4133bc444831", "vendor": {"name": "opencast"}}], "isExploited": false}